        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 4:21PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 421 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Westville, or 11 miles northeast of Lake Wateree Dam, moving east at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Torrential rain, wind gusts up to 50 mph, and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Camden, Lake Wateree Dam, Kershaw, Carolina Sandhills Wildlife
Refuge, Westville, Mt Pisgah, Longtown, Cassatt, Liberty Hill, Lake
Wateree State Park, Mcbee, Bethune, North Central High School,
Dekalb, Alligator Fire Station, Middendorf, Midway Elementary School,
Kershaw Correctional Institution, Lake Wateree near Highway 97, and
Ashland.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
